======================================================================
PART 5: FACTORIZATION OVER Z[q]
======================================================================

Q_3(q) = 6q + 2q^3 = 2q(3 + q^2)
  Roots: q=0 (mult 1), q=±i√3
  |roots| = 0, √3, √3
  √3 = KEY2^(1/2) ≈ 1.732051

Q_4(q) = 8q(3 + 2q^2 + 3q^4)
  Factor 3u^2 + 2u + 3 where u = q^2
  Discriminant = 4-36 = -32 < 0
  u = (-1 ± 2i√2)/3, |u| = √(1+8)/3 = √9/3 = 1
  ALL Q_4 zeros on unit circle! (Lee-Yang property)
  This confirms HYP-1243 at n=4.

Q_5(q) = 8(15q + 15q^3 + 30q^5 + 30q^9 + 15q^11 + 15q^13 + 8q^15)
  Inner polynomial coefficients (after q factor): [15, 0, 15, 0, 30, 0, 0, 0, 30, 0, 15, 0, 15, 0, 8]
  Reversed: [8, 0, 15, 0, 15, 0, 30, 0, 0, 0, 30, 0, 15, 0, 15]
  Palindromic? False

======================================================================
PART 6: DISCRIMINANT OF Q_n
======================================================================
Q_4 inner discriminant = -32 = -2^5
  -32 mod 7 = 3 (= 3 mod 7)
Q_3 inner discriminant = -12 = -4*3 = -(KEY1^2 * KEY2)

